Visible: "完善资料"`, it\'s a scalar value for `assertVisible`, and `optional` c
an\'t be a sibling in the command map. Actually it CAN in YAML, but Maestro\'s J
ackson parser might be configured differently.\n\nLet me fix all the files by co
nverting scalar-form commands with `optional` to map-form.\n\nWait, but I also n
eed to think about whether `optional` even exists for `assertVisible` in Maestro
1.39.13. Let me check if there\'s another way. In Maestro, you can use `runFlow`
with `when` condition, or you can just remove the optional assertions.\n\nActual
ly, a better approach for Maestro: `optional` works on `tapOn` and `swipe` but m
ight not work on `assertVisible`. For optional visibility checks, you might need
to use JavaScript or a different approach.\n\nLet me search the Maestro document
ation or try a different syntax.\n\nActually, I recall that in Maestro, you CAN 
